                            <comment id="14704696" author="erans" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 11:22:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The concept was of a &quot;counter&quot; rather than an &quot;incrementor&quot;; so the name is a bit misleading.&lt;br/&gt;
I can see that it could become an incrementor (where one would specify initial and final values, rather than count number).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But please raise this issue on the &quot;dev&quot; ML to get more opinions on whether this change is needed (preferably with a practical use-case), or whether it would suffice to forbid negative counts (by throwing an exception).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
